column5: well i woke up and wanted to fish so i loaded the boat and headed out with the wife in serch of bass and pan fish. Well it was a slow moring only one crappie and no bass. So i get a call from keith and he wants to come out and fish so i met him at the lanch and we headed out to get some crappies. The wind was blowing us all over and fianlly i broke out the ancher on a over hangin tree and it was non stop crappie! We put back a lot of small ones and kept a few for shore lunch!
Looks like a nice meal for 2.  Good going.
Some very fine eatin' there!!!  Was reading an article in In-Fisherman magazine that said Crappie move around and eat more than any other Sunfish in waters 41*F.
Nice catch guys !!!!...what time is dinner ???....cheers
Nice haul sleded, and thanks for not putting up pics of them battered and cooked on a plate. Those pics always make me hungry.
Nice work Eric gotta luv the Craps.
Great report and pics sleded  Thanks for sharing Leechman
You'll a shore lunch with that haul, thanks for the report...
Nice slabs for a feast boys and Sleded you were long overdue for a report
all those fish were caught in the same spot a big over hanging tree.
